post_text:
Breakfast and lunch are now free of charge for all Sayre students!

The USDA waiver announced earlier this week allows for free foodservice for all students through December 31st or as long as funding remains available.

Students will still be charged for extra items (i.e., additional milk or water.)

Meal statements will reflect charges through August and will still require payment.

Sayre Schools is excited to take part in this special opportunity for students and families!

post_text:
Middle School and High School Opening Week Information

Enrollment / Chromebook / Schedule pick up
Students who missed Chromeweek and have not enrolled need to stop by the office this Monday, Tuesday, or Wednesday between the hours of 8:00 a.m. and 3:00 p.m.

Open House night canceled
Due to the pandemic we have made the difficult decision to cancel our traditional Open House night. This will help us avoid risks associated with a large indoor gathering before launching the school year. Thank you for your understanding with this important precaution.

First day of school! Thursday, August 13th
First hour bell rings at 7:55 a.m.

Visitors
As we begin the school year, we are asking visitors to minimize entrance into our buildings. This protocol will help reduce the risk of exposure to students and personnel. (This includes parents/guardians)

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1A_yuv2OeiZyl4J6jPxMjwcO16hf5PugvtExbo9-X9j0/edit?usp=sharing

ACT Student
April 20 at 4:23 PM ·

In this time of uncertainty, it is clear that students need flexibility.

As CDC and local guidelines allow, we will offer flexible summer scheduling and test-at-home options beginning in late fall or early winter 2020.

Here's an overview of opportunities to take the ACT for the rest of the year:

- ACT National Test Dates: June 13 (make up date available June 20), July 18 (make up date available July 25), September 12, October 24, December 12

- ACT On-Campus Testing: Available at participating colleges and universities

- ACT Section Retesting: Available starting in September 2020

- ACT State and District Testing: Students who are testing as part of a state or district testing program should reach out to their school for the status of their testing

- ACT Test-At-Home Options: Available late fall/early winter 2020

Here is more information: https://bit.ly/3anf0jQ

post_text: Congratulations!! Cooper Rhoads & Blake Seymour! Sayre High School Alumni King & Queen!!
shared_text:
Sayre High School Alumni
April 1 at 11:11 AM ·

Even though we had to cancel our Alumni Celebration, The Alumni Association through the Sayre Chamber of Commerce, would still like to honor the Sayre Alumni King and Queen, Cooper Rhoads and Blake Seymour. Each will receive a $500 Scholarship to use at the college, university, or technical trade school of their choice. When enrolled in the Fall, please contact Sayre Chamber President Suzanne Hylton with your enrollment information. Thank you to everyone who participated, and we wish for the best for the Class of 2020... Stay Safe! Be sure to pick up a copy of the 88th Annual Alumni newspaper next week, both essays will be included.
Sincerely,
Amy (Loynd) Brinkley
Class of 1993

Sayre Public Schools will have their PreK enrollment on March 10th and 11th. Children who are age four on or before September 1st, are eligible for the PreK program at Sayre Early Childhood. Preferred enrollment hours are 8:00-11:00 a.m. and 12:30-2:30 p.m.

Any questions please call Mrs. Holland or Ms. Poole at 928-2013.

To: Parents of High School Juniors

FROM: Sayre ISD

Date: 8/27/2019

Sayre ISD is communicating with parents of students who will be juniors during the 2019-20 school year.

Our school district plans to administer the ACT® test in spring 2020 to eligible juniors as part of the state contract with the Oklahoma State Department of Education and ACT.

Last year over 95% of Oklahoma schools selected to administer the ACT. Our district believes this is an excellent opportunity for all eligible juniors to take the ACT at no cost to them or their families.

Additional information on why we chose the ACT can be found at 8 Reasons to Choose the ACT Test

Should you have any questions/comments, please contact Mary Lakey at 580-928-5531

Mary Lakey

Sayre ISD

DTC

post_text:
It’s the last weekend of summer! Here is a flashback video of the summer athletics 2018! Coach Filer says “I am extremely proud of the attendance, participation, and hard work both the boys and girls have put in this summer. Coach Radford has brought an energy that has benefited Sayre Athletics throughout the board. I am looking forward to seeing the process become the progress this year in our athletic programs.”
Coach Radford: “I am very proud of the effort put forth by all the athletes who attended summer pride. Those who attended are definitely better prepared for their seasons. The attendance award trip was a success and I’m glad that all the athletes and coaches had a great time.”
Hope everyone enjoyed their summer break!!
text:
It’s the last weekend of summer! Here is a flashback video of the summer athletics 2018! Coach Filer says “I am extremely proud of the attendance, participation, and hard work both the boys and girls have put in this summer. Coach Radford has brought an energy that has benefited Sayre Athletics throughout the board. I am looking forward to seeing the process become the progress this year in our athletic programs.”
Coach Radford: “I am very proud of the effort put forth by all the athletes who attended summer pride. Those who attended are definitely better prepared for their seasons. The attendance award trip was a success and I’m glad that all the athletes and coaches had a great time.”
Hope everyone enjoyed their summer break!!
